<details id="detail-bugs">
  <summary>🐛 Bugs &amp; Artifacts Introduced <span class="winner-tag">semver/goose WINS</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-content">
    <h4>pf-codemods: 2 Bugs + 1 Artifact</h4>
    
    <h4>Bug 1: Test Name Corruption (CRITICAL)</h4>
    <p>In <code>web/src/__tests__/types.spec.ts</code>, the codemod incorrectly replaced the string literal <code>'constructor'</code> in test description names:</p>
    <pre><code>// Before (main)
it('constructor', () =&gt; { ... })

// After (pf-codemods) — CORRUPTED
it("function Object() { [native code] }", () =&gt; { ... })</code></pre>
    <p>This occurred in 2 test cases (<code>URIRef</code> and <code>Node</code> describe blocks). The codemod evaluated <code>'constructor'</code> as a prototype property access rather than a plain string literal. While tests still pass (the test name doesn't affect execution), the test descriptions are now meaningless and mask the actual test intent.</p>
    
    <h4>Bug 2: ESLint Cache File Committed</h4>
    <p><code>.cache_1l6xbui</code> — a large ESLint cache JSON file was accidentally committed. This file does not exist on <code>main</code> and should never be tracked in version control. It should be added to <code>.gitignore</code>.</p>
    
    <h4>Bug 3: Formatting Regression</h4>
    <p>In <code>TimeRangeDropdown.tsx</code>, the codemod changed indentation from 2-space to tab indentation for the import block, creating inconsistency with the rest of the codebase.</p>
    
    <h4>semver/goose: 0 Bugs</h4>
    <p>No test corruption, no artifacts committed, no formatting regressions.</p>
    
    <table>
      <tr><th>Issue</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
